From 0dd3a1cf5068c64905df5bc41834834c41e40fc4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Jul 2025 09:52:15 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:HOSTAPD: Assign conf->opclass during CSA failure
 after DFS radar

When DFS radar is injected on an AP operating on a 5 GHz channel 52
in 20 MHz bandwidth, the AP goes down if the random target channel
selected for post-radar operation, is DFS.

The failure is observed in configured_fixed_chan_to_freq
(a sub-function of setup_interface2) as the opclass is incorrect for
the channel in which the AP is brought up.

This is because, in hostapd_dfs_request_channel_switch, when
hostapd_switch_channel returns a failure, the conf's channel number,
frequency, secondary channel, and bandwidth are set to those of the
parameters of the new target channel, but the conf->op_class is not
updated. Due to this, when configured_fixed_chan_to_freq is called as
part of hostapd_iface_enable, the conf->op_class does not match the
conf->channel.

To fix this issue, in hostapd_dfs_request_channel_switch,
set the conf->op_class to that of the new target channel.

Tag: DFS
Patch-dependency: r63-UPSTREAM-HOSTAPD-Update-conf-op_class-in-hostapd_cha.patch

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/dfs.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/dfs.c b/src/ap/dfs.c
index 602301f..96d91fa 100644
--- a/src/ap/dfs.c
+++ b/src/ap/dfs.c
@@ -1105,7 +1105,7 @@ int hostapd_is_dfs_chan_available(struct hostapd_iface *iface)
 
 
 static int hostapd_dfs_request_channel_switch(struct hostapd_iface *iface,
-					      int channel, int freq,
+					      u8 channel, int freq,
 					      int secondary_channel,
 					      u8 current_vht_oper_chwidth,
 					      u8 oper_centr_freq_seg0_idx,
@@ -1175,6 +1175,8 @@ static int hostapd_dfs_request_channel_switch(struct hostapd_iface *iface,
 	}
 
 	if (num_err == iface->num_bss) {
+		u8 op_class = 0;
+
 		wpa_printf(MSG_WARNING,
 			   "DFS failed to schedule CSA (%d) - trying fallback",
 			   err);
@@ -1186,6 +1188,11 @@ static int hostapd_dfs_request_channel_switch(struct hostapd_iface *iface,
 						     oper_centr_freq_seg0_idx);
 		hostapd_set_oper_centr_freq_seg1_idx(iface->conf,
 						     oper_centr_freq_seg1_idx);
+		if (ieee80211_freq_to_channel_ext(freq, secondary_channel,
+						  new_vht_oper_chwidth,
+						  &op_class, &channel) !=
+		    NUM_HOSTAPD_MODES)
+			iface->conf->op_class = op_class;
 
 		hostapd_disable_iface(iface);
 		hostapd_enable_iface(iface);
-- 
